props.activeClass: Class bound when component is active. **warning** Depending upon the component, this could cause side effects. If you need to add a custom class on top of a default, just do `active-class="default-class your-class"
props.exact: Exactly match the link. Without this, '/' will match every route
props.href: Will designate the component tag to `<a>`
props.nuxt: Specifies the link is a nuxt-link
props.to: Will designate the component tag to `<router-link>`
props.tag: Specify a custom tag to use on the component
